\exercice*

Commençons par résoudre séparément les deux inéquations.

\begin{minipage}[b]{.4\textwidth}
\begin{align*}
\numprint{-7}\,x+\numprint{3} & ≤ \numprint{-9}\,x+\numprint{6} \\
    \numprint{-7}\,x+\numprint{3} \textcolor{blue}{\numprint{+9}\,x} & ≤ \numprint{-9}\,x+\numprint{6} \textcolor{blue}{\numprint{+9}\,x}\\
\numprint{2}\,x+\numprint{3} & ≤ \numprint{6} \\
    \numprint{2}\,x+\numprint{3} \textcolor{blue}{-\numprint{3}} & ≤ \numprint{6} \textcolor{blue}{-\numprint{3}}\\
\numprint{2}\,x & ≤ \numprint{3} \\
    \numprint{2}\,x \textcolor{blue}{\div \numprint{2}} & ≤ \numprint{3} \textcolor{blue}{\div \numprint{2}}\\
  x & ≤ \frac{\numprint{3}}{\numprint{2}} \\
\end{align*}
\end{minipage}%
\hfill%
\begin{minipage}[b]{.4\textwidth}
\begin{align*}
\numprint{-2}\,x+\numprint{1} & > \numprint{-7}\,x-\numprint{3} \\
    \numprint{-2}\,x+\numprint{1} \textcolor{blue}{\numprint{+7}\,x} & > \numprint{-7}\,x-\numprint{3} \textcolor{blue}{\numprint{+7}\,x}\\
\numprint{5}\,x+\numprint{1} & > -\numprint{3} \\
    \numprint{5}\,x+\numprint{1} \textcolor{blue}{-\numprint{1}} & > -\numprint{3} \textcolor{blue}{-\numprint{1}}\\
\numprint{5}\,x & > -\numprint{4} \\
    \numprint{5}\,x \textcolor{blue}{\div \numprint{5}} & > -\numprint{4} \textcolor{blue}{\div \numprint{5}}\\
  x & > -\frac{\numprint{4}}{\numprint{5}} \\
\end{align*}
\end{minipage}%

Les solutions sont donc \textcolor{blue}{$x≤\frac{\numprint{3}}{\numprint{2}}$} et \textcolor{Green}{$x>-\frac{\numprint{4}}{\numprint{5}}$}, dont voici la représentation sur la droite des réels.

\begin{center}
    \begin{tikzpicture}[line width=2pt, xscale=1]
      \draw[-Stealth] ( -6, 0) -- ( 6, 0);
      \foreach \x in { -5, 0, ..., 5}{
          \draw (\x, -.2) -- (\x, .2);
          \path (\x, 0) node[above=5pt]{$\x$};
      }
      \foreach \x in { -5, ..., 5}{
          \draw[line width=1.5pt] (\x, -.15) -- (\x, .15);
      }
      \begin{scope}[blue]
          \path ( 3/2, 0) node[below=9pt]{$\frac{\numprint{3}}{\numprint{2}}$};
          \draw[arrows={Bracket[scale=1.5, inset=3pt,]-},yshift=-2pt]
               ($
                  ( 3/2, 0)
                  +
                      (.5pt, 0)
               $)
               --
 ( -6, 0)                ;
      \end{scope}
      \begin{scope}[Green]
          \path ( -4/5, 0) node[below=9pt]{$-\frac{\numprint{4}}{\numprint{5}}$};
          \draw[arrows={Bracket[scale=1.5,reversed]-},yshift=-4pt]
               ($
                  ( -4/5, 0)
                  +
                      (-4.5pt, 0)
               $)
               --
 ( 5.6, 0)                ;
      \end{scope}
  \end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

Puisque nous voulons
 l'intersection des deux solutions (car $x≤\frac{\numprint{3}}{\numprint{2}}$ \textbf{et} $x>-\frac{\numprint{4}}{\numprint{5}}$), alors nous cherchons les parties de la droite des réels surlignées
 deux fois. Les solutions sont donc :
\[
    x \in \left]-\frac{\numprint{4}}{\numprint{5}} ; \frac{\numprint{3}}{\numprint{2}}\right]
\]